      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. so if the acidity messes with the enzymes and the calcium, does that mean the burning is actually a warning sign that the muscle is about to stop working properly? like, is there a limit to how much buildup the cells can actually handle before they just shut down?",
      "source": "evaluator"
